Data availability

            Daily climate data during the period 1960–2020 derived from the Climate Research Unit–National Center for Environmental Prediction (CRUNCEP) 6-hourly climate datasets (https://vesg.ipsl.upmc.fr). Annual atmospheric CO2 concentration from 1960 to 2016 was obtained from the NOAA GLOBALVIEW-CO2 dataset (https://www.esrl.noaa.gov). Projected future temperature and precipitation data were obtained from the Inter-Sectoral Impact Model Intercomparison Project (https://data.isimip.org/search/). Global synthetic N and P fertilizer data (1960–2020) are available via PANGAEA at https://doi.org/10.1594/PANGAEA.863323 (ref. 38) and figshare at https://doi.org/10.6084/m9.figshare.25435432.v3 (ref. 39). Global manure data (1960–2014) are available via PANGAEA at https://doi.org/10.1594/PANGAEA.871980 (ref. 40). Tillage practices data were collected from ref. 41 (https://doi.org/10.5880/PIK.2019.009). Data on the meta-analysis process dataset and parameters can be found in the Supplementary Information. The compiled global dataset and the result maps generated in this study are available via figshare at https://doi.org/10.6084/m9.figshare.28180565.v2 (ref. 51). Source data are provided with this paper.
          Code availability

            The code for applying the trained random forest models to generate regional predictions is available via figshare at https://doi.org/10.6084/m9.figshare.28180565.v2 (ref. 51). The training data and model development scripts can be shared upon reasonable request. We conducted statistical analyses and other computations using RStudio version 2023.03.1.
